# Premitive Data Types

Boolean: True or false. It stores flag vlaues either true or false.
String: 'Hello World'. It stores the string values.
Integer: 12345. It is 32 bit iteger and stores integer/number values and upto 2^32.
Long: 12345. It is 64 bit iteger and stores integer/number values and upto 2^64.
Decimal: 10.2. It is 32 bit iteger and stores integer/number values and upto 2^32.
Double: 10.2. It is 64 bit iteger and stores integer/number values and upto 2^64.string myString = 'Hello world';
System.debug(myString);

boolean myBool = true;
System.debug(myBool);

integer myInteger = 627;
System.debug(myInteger);

long myLong = 1000000000L;
System.debug(myLong);

decimal myDecimal = 1.2;
System.debug(myDecimal);

double myDouble = 1.222222222D;
System.debug(myDouble);

Date myDate = Date.newInstance(2024, 02, 3);
System.debug(myDate);

Time myTime = Time.newInstance(14, 45, 22, 11);
System.debug(myTime);

Datetime myDateTime = Datetime.newInstance(2024, 02, 3, 02, 11, 22);
System.debug(myDateTime);
